item.title: What will happen if i change C:\Documents and Settings\Sean\ to adifferent name?
item.dc:creator: @VB7_Rocks VB7 Rocks
item.description:
@VB7_Rocks wrote:

[quote=“poopy4231, post:1, topic:10626”]What will happen if i change C:\Documents and Settings\Sean\ to adifferent name?

like

C:\Documents and Settings\Sean pooper\

will some programs not work? or anything bad happen?[/quote]

I don’t think you can change the name of an active account, but if you have done a repair install of Windows and you have like an archived account in there but it’s an inactive account then I think it might let you change it. I’m not sure though.

Note: I was able to change Guest and Administrator without any noticable difference, though I haven’t tried logging in as them, but whenever I try to change my own folder’s name, I get the same error as therealjdb, who posted above me.

Here is his post, which shows the exact error message that I get too.

[quote=“therealjdb, post:2, topic:10626”]

It doesnt let me change my name. Have you actually tried, I didnt think you could.[/quote]
